text: Ron Moss (13 June 1922 - 22 October 2004) was an Australian cricketer. He played three first-class matches for New South Wales in 1948/49. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1922 births Category:2004 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Sydney
